ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Windows Common Controls MSCOMCTL.OCX Remote Code Execution

EngDesc.value: A remote code execution vulnerability exists in Microsoft Windows Common Controls. The vulnerability is due to insufficient validation by the ActiveX control MSCOMCTL.TabStrip.This vulnerability can be exploited by remote, unauthenticated attackers by enticing a user to open a malicious document. Successful exploitation could result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the currently logged on user.
